1. Calculate total & average for each student 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Data:
students = {
    "Asha": {"Math": 78, "Science": 85, "English": 67},
    "Ravi": {"Math": 35, "Science": 40, "English": 50},
    "John": {"Math": 90, "Science": 92, "English": 88}
}

Code:
results = {}
for name, scores in students.items():
    total = sum(scores.values())
    average = total / len(scores.values())
    results[name] = {"Total": total, "Average": round(average, 2)} # nested dictionary
print(results)
for name, data in results.items():
    print(f"{name} : {data}")

Output:
{'Asha': {'Total': 230, 'Average': 76.67}, 'Ravi': {'Total': 125, 'Average': 41.67}, 'John': {'Total': 270, 'Average': 90.0}}
